HEADWORD: belly up
<hw>bel"ly up`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>to approach (a counter) and
stand in front of it; -- used mostly in the phrase <col><b>belly up to
the bar</b></col> (i.e. to a counter in a saloon).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

